it would be nice to be able to "disable" services, rather than removing them.  if for some reason one want to pause a service for an indefinite time, the only options are to delete and recreate, or to set a very large delay, which works but is a little hackish.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-1451].
  {panel}

When Adding a POP mail server, the user should be allowed to use a JNDI session, just like with SMTP configuration.

I'm running JIRA to support our development effort.  I don't have control over a real mail server so I've had to install JAMES on our development server using custom ports.  The custom ports for SMTP and POP are specified in the setup of the mail session.  However, the POP service does not use the mail session.

